2154521.description:
Jozi Linux User Group (or JoziLUG) is a group for Linux geeks to meetup, listen to an awesome talk about open source technologies and chat. Our goal is to grow a vibrant, supportive Linux user and Open Source community in South Africa.

We meet on the 3rd Monday of every month. Meetings take the form of one or more presentations followed by discussion, dinner and drinks. The talks start at 18:30 and generally end by 20:30, but people are encouraged to stick around afterward and chat with fellow geeks.

If you're keen to get involved, let us know. Suggested topics for presentations are also welcome!
